# UJL Documentation Consistency

## Goal

Ensure all relevant documentation surfaces stay current and consistent with implemented behavior.

## Must

- When behavior, API, architecture, workflow, or standards change, verify and update all relevant documentation surfaces:
  - Developer docs (`README*`, `CONTRIBUTING.md`, `AGENTS.md`)
  - Agentic instructions (`.agents/rules/*`, `.agents/skills/*`, subagent definitions if present)
  - Documentation website (`apps/docs`)
- Keep terminology aligned across code and all touched documentation.
- Keep links and referenced paths valid in changed docs/instructions.
- Avoid contradictory guidance between documentation surfaces.

## Should

- Add concise migration notes when contributor workflow or architecture expectations changed.
- Reference canonical sources instead of duplicating long guidance in multiple places.
- Prefer small, focused doc updates in the same branch as the code change.

## Avoid

- Updating only one documentation surface for cross-cutting changes.
- Leaving stale package paths, scripts, or workflow references.
- Introducing new guidance in skills/rules without reflecting it in contributor-facing docs when relevant.

## Allowed Exceptions

- Purely local refactors with no behavior/workflow/contract change can skip doc edits.
- Experimental branches may defer broad doc updates if the PR clearly marks follow-up work.
